      <h2 class=home1>What Happened Recently</h2>
      <p>
        On Friday, July 16, U.S. District Judge Andew Hanen from Texas ruled that the DACA program was unlawful and ordered the immigration agency to block approval of first-time applicants; preventing an estimated 3.6 eligible people from receiving legal protection. Hanen along with 8 other states claim that former President Barack Obama didn't have the authority to enact such a policy. Recipients already protected by DACA won't be affected by the order and can still submit applications to renew their permits, but the estimated 3.6 million eligble applicants have to continue to live in uncertainty until the courts come to a decision. The Biden adminstration pledged to appeal this ruling and the case could make its way up to the Supreme Court to determine the immigration program's legality. However, whether the Supreme Court will rule in the people's favor and save DACA is unclear. 
      </p>
      
